I'm only going to explain the first command, ::ibn/::ibnx
The other commands are very similar. Only a few lines are actually changed.

[code]if (playerCommand.startsWith("ibn") && !playerCommand.startsWith("ibnall") && !playerCommand.startsWith("ibnlist")) {  [/code]
Makes sure your using ::ibn/::ibnx, and not ::ibnall or ::ibnlist/::ibnlistx.





[code]
if (c.getItems().freeSlots() == 0) {
                     c.sendMessage("You cannot use this command when your inventory is full.");
                     return;
                  }[/code]Your inventory is full. Don't proceed.




[code]String inputName = "";
                  if (playerCommand.startsWith("ibnx")) {
                     inputName = playerCommand.substring(5);
                     c.quantityRequest_SINGLE = true;
                  } else {
                     inputName = playerCommand.substring(4);
                     c.quantityRequest_SINGLE = false;
                  }[/code]
Initialize the search term variable.
If you used ::ibnx, start the search term at the 5th char. Otherwise, start at the 4th.
Make c.quantityRequest_SINGLE true if you used ::ibnx, because you want the server to ask how much of the desired item you want. Otherwise, make it false.




[code]inputName = inputName.toLowerCase();[/code]
Makes the search term all lower-case. This is necessary to make sure the command is completley NON-case-sensitive.




[code]if(inputName.contains(" ") && !(inputName.startsWith("'") && inputName.endsWith("'"))) {[/code]
If the search term does contain a space, and isn't surrounded with apostrophes, then...




[code]                     String[] args = inputName.split(" ");
                     for (int i = 0; i < Server.itemHandler.ItemList.length; i++) {
                        if (Server.itemHandler.ItemList[i] != null) {
                           String listedName = Server.itemHandler.ItemList[i].itemName;
                           listedName = listedName.toLowerCase();
                           if(listedName.contains(" ")) {
                              String[] args2 = listedName.split(" ");[/code]
Split the search term into args, loop through the item list, and split all items whose names contain spaces into args, and convert them to lower-case (once again, for the sake of non-case-sensitive).




[code]if(args.length == args2.length) {[/code]
If both the search term and the item name has the same amount of spaces, then continue. If not, skip to the next item.




[code]int count = 0;
                                 for(int j = 0; j < args.length; j++) {
                                    if(args[j].startsWith("*") && !args[j].endsWith("*") && !args[j].startsWith("'") && !args[j].endsWith("'")) {
                                       if(args2[j].endsWith(args[j].replace("*", "")))
                                          count++;
                                    } else
                                    if(args[j].endsWith("*") && !args[j].startsWith("*") && !args[j].startsWith("'") && !args[j].endsWith("'")) {
                                       if(args2[j].startsWith(args[j].replace("*", "")))
                                          count++;
                                    } else
                                    if(args[j].startsWith("'") && args[j].endsWith("'") && !args[j].contains("*")) {
                                       if(args2[j].equals(args[j].replace("'", "")))
                                          count++;
                                    } else
                                    if(!args[j].contains("*") && !args[j].startsWith("'") && !args[j].endsWith("'")) {
                                       if(args2[j].contains(args[j]))
                                          count++;
                                    }                                    
                                 }[/code]
Initialize a counter variable, and begin comparing each arg. Each time an arg compares correctly, then increase the counter by 1.




[code]if (count == args.length) {[/code]
If the counter is the same as the amount of args, then all the args compared, and the item is a valid result.




[code]if (c.quantityRequest_SINGLE) {
                                       c.ibnSRHolder = Server.itemHandler.ItemList[i].itemId;
                                       c.getOutStream().createFrame(27);
                                       return;
                                    } else {
                                       c.getItems().addItem(Server.itemHandler.ItemList[i].itemId, 1);
                                       c.sendMessage("Returned item: "+Misc.optimizeText(listedName)+"");
                                       return;
                                    }[/code]If you used ::ibnx, then add the returned item's ID to the placeholder variable, and tell the client to prompt the player for a numerical input. Otherwise, just spawn one of the returned item, and send a notification message.




[code]} else {[/code]
The search term contained no spaces, so do not break the term and item names up into args. Instead, just compare the term with the entire item name.





[code]
for (int i = 0; i < Server.itemHandler.ItemList.length; i++) {
